  "blurb": "A 425 m² villa stepped down a quiet Plai Laem hillside, built around a long infinity pool that runs out toward the sea and the islands beyond — vaulted teak ceilings, glass walls that fold away to the breeze, a shaded sala on its own terrace, live-in staff who cook breakfast and lunch each day, and airport transfers both ways.",
  "detail": "This four-bedroom villa sits high in a quiet residential enclave on the Plai Laem headland, arranged over stepped terraces so that almost every room looks out across tropical hillside to the water and the islands beyond. It measures 425 m², and the design is unhurried island-modern: high vaulted timber ceilings, floor-to-ceiling glass that slides away to let the breeze through, and a plan that never quite settles on where the inside ends.\n\nThe main pavilion holds an open-plan living and dining area alongside a full white kitchen with an island, breakfast bar and double ovens, all of it framed by sea views. The living space opens directly onto the pool terrace, and a separate open-air sala — cantilevered over the slope on its own deck, with daybeds and lounge seating — makes a cooler spot for reading or a late lunch out of the sun.\n\nA long infinity pool is the centre of the property, its far edge dissolving into the view, with sun loungers and a woven daybed along the deck and frangipani planted through the terrace. There is a barbecue for evenings outside and a pool table indoors for when the afternoon heat wins.\n\nThe four bedrooms are air-conditioned and quietly finished, with en-suite bathrooms in cream stone, walk-in rain showers, twin vanities and generous hanging space. The villa comes with staff living on site: daily housekeeping, a cook who prepares breakfast every morning and lunch on request, and a concierge for tours, boats and restaurant bookings. Round-trip airport transfers are included, and a cot and high chair can be arranged. Dinner service is available for a small charge on top of ingredients.",
